They first saw it when I went on a vacation with them a few years ago. I had to wear short sleeves because it was crazy hot and obviously all my family noticed. At first they were really obsessed with it and were excessively talking about it like it would help me (jeez i just wanted enjoy my trip yk). But after the years, after my few hospitalisations, they understood a little bit the whole subject of self harm and became more open minded with it. I told them I hated how they said things to me and they understood that as well. Self harm is something the family needs to understand and accept. It doesn’t mean they won’t help or stop me from doing it. I know they are not okay with it and that it hurts them, but at least they understand.
